The market value balance sheet is a tool used to show and compute the current market value of the firm based on their assets and debt. For this firm, since it is an all-equity firm, then it means that it has no debt. We will then solve only for the assets of this firm.

The assets of this firm can be simply solved by taking the number of outstanding shares and multiplying the current price per share.

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Assets}&=\text{Outstanding shares} \times \text{Price per share}
\end{aligned}$$
